Certain races get hide and/or sneak as <b>race</b> skills, and certain classes also get hide/sneak as <b>class</b> skills.

If you get them as a race skill, they will start at 50 and will never increase.

If you get them as a class skill, you will be able to increase them normally.

So druids don't get hide or sneak as class skills, but halflings do get them as race skills - so as a halfling druid you will start at 50 skill in both and will never be able to increase them. 

If you were halfling of a class which did get them as class skills, e.g. a ranger (get sneak at lvl 10, hide at 25) you would still start with 50 skill, but once you got to a high enough level in the class you would then be able to start increasing the skill above 50.

Hope this makes sense!

